                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.6341 South American Development Co./58a:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gade</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-02-04T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 4, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. The representatives of the South American Development Company discussed with
                    the Department this afternoon the problems confronting them. They indicated a
                    willingness to consider sympathetically the urgent financial needs of the
                    Government and to attempt to work out an arrangement satisfactory to all
                    concerned. However a period of 2 weeks will be required for full consideration
                    by the Board of Directors and for Tweedy’s return to Ecuador when he will be
                    prepared to discuss with the Government all aspects of the problem. You are
                    therefore requested to express to the Minister for Foreign Affairs the earnest
                    hope of this Government that the President will find it possible to grant the
                    necessary extension of time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
